                <Header>Moving Companies</Header>
                <Paragraph>A moving company is responsible if it loses or damages a customer’s household possessions during the move. The customer may file a claim with the mover to request financial compensation for the loss or damage. If the moving company denies the claim—in whole or in part—the customer may need to file a lawsuit or pursue arbitration to obtain compensation. In this type of situation, the customer may need to hire an attorney.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
